id: pm-xzhz
title: Expose SDK runAction and PmClient execution surface for programmatic integrations
description: "Promote the existing pm_run-style action dispatcher into the public SDK runtime so integrations can execute pm actions without shelling out, and have MCP reuse the SDK path. Duplicate check: searched all statuses for PmClient/runAction/high-level execution/GH-439; only the broad pm-usfg epic and primitive-family features matched, with no exact child item."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: agent-ux,architecture,"area:sdk",token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-07-05T18:26:14.911Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-06T05:12:58.532Z"
author: codex-agent
acceptance_criteria: SDK runtime exports typed runAction and PmClient surfaces; MCP pm_run and narrow tools dispatch through the same SDK path; docs and tests cover create/list/get/update/close style execution in-process; temp-project proof shows a consumer can use @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk/runtime without spawning pm.
parent: pm-usfg
resolution: "Promoted the MCP action dispatcher into src/sdk/runtime.ts as the public runAction/PmClient execution surface, updated MCP to reuse it, documented SDK usage, and covered the in-process installed-package path."
expected_result: "SDK consumers can import @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk/runtime and execute common pm actions without spawning pm, while MCP behavior stays aligned and quality gates remain green."
actual_result: PmClient/runAction completed create/list/search/get/update/context/close in unit coverage and in a fresh installed-package temp consumer; MCP focused tests and full 100% coverage passed.
